                            <h2 style="color: #1F497D; font-size: 7.2pt; margin-bottom: 10pt; margin-top: 20pt;">2.1 Membership Formalities</h2>
                            <p style="font-size: 6pt; letter-spacing: 0.1pt; line-height: 12px; margin-bottom: 10pt;">
                                Any person who applies for this Scheme and hereafter named as proposed life to be assured, must give his/her consent thereto and satisfy the requirements as to his/her state of health by filling in, dating and signing an appropriate membership application form which will be remitted to him/her by ABSA Bank (Mauritius) Ltd. In every case, the admission is subject to the approval of the Insurer who reserves the right to have the person undergo a medical examination in relation to the declaration made by him/her in respect of his/her state of health or his/her age or the amount assured (including any amount already assured).
                            </p>
                            <h2 style="color: #1F497D; font-size: 7.2pt; margin-bottom: 10pt; margin-top: 10pt;">2.2 Extra Risks</h2>
                            <p style="font-size: 6pt; letter-spacing: 0.1pt; line-height: 12px; margin-bottom: 10pt;">
                                In case the Insurer decides, in the light of the declaration of health or the result of the medical examination to apply a special rate, the insurance cover will become effective only after the written consent of the proposed life to be assured has been received or the appropriate premium has been paid. Counter offer letters will be sent by the Insurer to ABSA Bank (Mauritius) Ltd who will request for written consent of the proposed life to be assured.
                            </p>
                            <h2 style="color: #1F497D; font-size: 7.2pt; margin-bottom: 10pt; margin-top: 10pt;">2.3 Effective Date</h2>
                            <p style="font-size: 6pt; letter-spacing: 0.1pt; line-height: 12px; margin-bottom: 5pt;">
                                In case the proposed life to be assured has signed the membership application form and the health declaration does not reveal any adverse features, the insurance cover takes effect as from the date the credit facility is disbursed and the membership application form is signed and attested by the seal of ABSA Bank (Mauritius) Ltd.
                            </p>
                            <p style="font-size: 6pt; letter-spacing: 0.1pt; line-height: 12px; margin-bottom: 10pt;">
                                In any other cases, if the proposed life to be assured has been unable to provide the membership application form and health declaration applicable in his case, or if the sum to be guaranteed exceeds non-medical limit and a medical examination has been required (with or without any supplementary examination or medical tests), the insurance cover will take effect as from the date the credit facility is disbursed subject to the Insurer notifying his acceptance.
                            </p>
                            <ul style="list-style: none; padding-left: 20pt;">
                                <li style=" margin-bottom: 5pt; font-size: 6pt; letter-spacing: 0.1pt; line-height: 12px;">
                                    a) war, invasion, act of foreign enemy, hostilities or warlike operations (whether war be declared or not), civil war, military rising, insurrection, rebellion, revolution, military or usurped power, martial law, mutiny or riot or civil commotion assuming the proportions of or amounting to a popular rising,
                                </li>
                                <li style=" margin-bottom: 5pt; font-size: 6pt; letter-spacing: 0.1pt; line-height: 12px;">
                                    b) acts of terrorism or action taken in controlling, preventing, suppressing or in any way relating to any act of terrorism, regardless of any other cause or event contributing concurrently or in any other sequence of the loss. An act of terrorism means an act – whether involving violence or the use of force or not – or the threat or the preparation thereof, of any person or group(s) of persons – whether acting alone or on behalf of or in connection with any organisation(s) or government (s) – which appears to be intended to intimidate or influence a de jure or de facto government or the public or a section of the public, or disrupt any segment of the economy and from its nature or context is done in connection with political, social, religious, ideological or similar causes or objectives.
                                </li>
                                <li style=" margin-bottom: 5pt; font-size: 6pt; letter-spacing: 0.1pt; line-height: 12px;">
                                    c) nuclear reaction, nuclear radiation.
                                </li>
                            </ul>
                            <h2 style="color: #1F497D; font-size: 7.2pt; margin-bottom: 10pt; margin-top: 10pt;">2.3 Effective Date</h2>
                            <p style="font-size: 6pt; letter-spacing: 0.1pt; line-height: 12px; margin-bottom: 5pt;">
                                In case the proposed life to be assured has signed the membership application form and the health declaration does not reveal any adverse features, the insurance cover takes effect as from the date the credit facility is disbursed and the membership application form is signed and attested by the seal of ABSA Bank (Mauritius) Ltd.
                            </p>
                            <h2 style="color: #1F497D; font-size: 7.2pt; margin-bottom: 10pt; margin-top: 10pt;">8.0. CLAIMS</h2>
                            <p style="font-size: 6pt; letter-spacing: 0.1pt; line-height: 12px; margin-bottom: 5pt;">
                                The amount payable upon the death or total and permanent disability of the Life Assured is the actual amount of capital outstanding at the time of the event as certified by ABSA Bank (Mauritius) Ltd.
                            </p>
                            <p style="font-size: 6pt; letter-spacing: 0.1pt; line-height: 12px; margin-bottom: 5pt;">
                                The Insurer will not be liable for any arrears or late payments by the Assured to ABSA Bank (Mauritius) Ltd, which will have for effect to increase the amount of outstanding capital at date of death or total and permanent disability.
                            </p>
                            <h2 style="color: #1F497D; font-size: 7.2pt; margin-bottom: 10pt; margin-top: 10pt;">8.1. Claims formalities</h2>
                            <p style="font-size: 6pt; letter-spacing: 0.1pt; line-height: 12px; margin-bottom: 5pt;">
                                Claims arising on death or total and permanent disability should be notified by ABSA Bank (Mauritius) Ltd as soon as possible and be supported by the relevant birth certificate (and marriage certificate in the case of the married female Life Assured) and the following documents:
                            </p>
                            <ul style="list-style: none; padding-left: 15pt;">
                                <li style=" margin-bottom: 10pt; font-size: 6pt; letter-spacing: 0.1pt; line-height: 12px;">
                                    a) In case of death, the relevant death certificate and a medical certificate indicating the exact cause of death.
                                </li>
                                <li style=" margin-bottom: 10pt; font-size: 6pt; letter-spacing: 0.1pt; line-height: 12px;">
                                    b) In case of disability, a medical certificate indicating the state of disability.
                                </li>
                                <li style=" margin-bottom: 10pt; font-size: 6pt; letter-spacing: 0.1pt; line-height: 12px;">
                                    c) In case of disappearance of the Life Assured in circumstances provided for by article 133 & following Code Napoléon, the Insurer will pay the guaranteed capital, on presentation of a duly certified copy of the declarative decision of death pronounced by a Judge in Chambers and transcribed in compliance with the provisions of the Civil Status Act.
                                </li>
                            </ul>
                            <p style="font-size: 6pt; letter-spacing: 0.1pt; line-height: 12px; margin-bottom: 5pt;">
                                Any action arising out of this policy is time-barred five years after the date of the occurrence giving rise to it in accordance with the provisions of Articles 1983-37 and 1983-38 of the Code Civil.
                            </p>
                            <h2 style="color: #1F497D; font-size: 7.2pt; margin-bottom: 10pt; margin-top: 10pt;">9.0 COOLING OFF PERIOD</h2>
                        </td>
