                            </p>
                            <h2 style="color: #1F497D; font-size: 7.2pt; margin-bottom: 10pt;">4.0 TERMINATION OF MEMBERSHIP</h2>
                            <p style="font-size: 6pt; letter-spacing: 0.1pt; line-height: 12px; margin-bottom: 10pt;">
                                The insurance cover ceases, at latest, in respect of the Life Assured at zero hour on: The 70th anniversary of birth as regards death cover and the 65th anniversary of birth as regards total and permanent disability cover;
                            </p>
                            <ul style="padding-left: 20pt;">
                                <li style=" margin-bottom: 5pt; font-size: 6pt; letter-spacing: 0.1pt; line-height: 12px;">cessation of premium payment;</li>
                                <li style=" margin-bottom: 5pt; font-size: 6pt; letter-spacing: 0.1pt; line-height: 12px;">or, at the earliest, on the date on which he/she has fully repaid his/her approved credit facility.</li>
                            </ul>
                            <p style="font-size: 6pt; letter-spacing: 0.1pt; line-height: 12px; margin-bottom: 10pt;">
                                Unless specified otherwise in the policy, no benefits will become payable on the termination of cover of a Life Assured consequent to an event specified above.
                            </p>
                            <h2 style="color: #1F497D; font-size: 7.2pt; margin-bottom: 10pt;">5.0 SUM ASSURED</h2>
                            <p style="font-size: 6pt; letter-spacing: 0.1pt; line-height: 12px; margin-bottom: 10pt;">
                                If the Life Assured dies or becomes totally and permanently disabled after the date the cover on his life commenced, the Insurer shall pay to ABSA Bank (Mauritius) Ltd the sum assured in respect of the Life Assured.
                            </p>
                            <p style="font-size: 6pt; letter-spacing: 0.1pt; line-height: 12px; margin-bottom: 10pt;">
                                In case of total and permanent disability, the claim amount due by the Insurer in respect of the claim will be calculated on the basis of the outstanding balance calculated on the day when the Insurer can medically certify in Mauritius the condition of the Life Assured.
                            </p>
                            <p style="font-size: 6pt; letter-spacing: 0.1pt; line-height: 12px; margin-bottom: 10pt;">
                                The sum assured in respect of a Life Assured is equal to the outstanding capital amount of the credit facility at the time of the claim as per the Individual Schedule.
                            </p>
                            <p style="font-size: 6pt; letter-spacing: 0.1pt; line-height: 12px; margin-bottom: 10pt;">
                                If death or total and permanent disability occurs during the cover period, the sum assured payable should not exceed the outstanding capital amount of the credit facility as per the Individual Schedule.
                            </p>
                            <p style="font-size: 6pt; letter-spacing: 0.1pt; line-height: 12px; margin-bottom: 10pt;">
                                Within a period of 30 days from the day you receive this policy, you have the right to change your mind by returning the policy and informing in writing ABSA Bank (Mauritius) Ltd that you DO NOT intend to proceed with the insurance cover and you shall be entitled to a refund of the premiums paid, net of the cost of any medical examinations paid on your behalf.
                            </p>
