                            <h2 style="color: #1F497D; font-size: 7.2pt; margin-bottom: 10pt;">6.0 RISKS COVERED – RISKS EXCLUDED</h2>
                            <h2 style="color: #1F497D; font-size: 7.2pt; margin-bottom: 10pt;">6.1 Death Risks</h2>
                            <p style="font-size: 6pt; letter-spacing: 0.1pt; line-height: 12px; margin-bottom: 10pt;">
                                All death risks, whatever be the cause, are covered subject to the following exclusions:
                            </p>
                            <ul style="list-style: none; padding-left: 15pt;">
                                <li style=" margin-bottom: 10pt; font-size: 6pt; letter-spacing: 0.1pt; line-height: 12px;">
                                    a) Suicide: Voluntary and conscious suicide is only covered after one year.
                                </li>
                                <li style=" margin-bottom: 10pt; font-size: 6pt; letter-spacing: 0.1pt; line-height: 12px;">
                                    b) Aerial acrobatics, records or attempts at records, preparatory attempt of reception attempt as well as practice of delta-plane or parachute and more generally all aeronautic sports are not covered by the guarantee.
                                </li>
                            </ul>
                            <p style="font-size: 6pt; letter-spacing: 0.1pt; line-height: 12px; margin-bottom: 10pt;">
                                It is specified however that the use, as a common passenger or as a crew member, of any public air transport and operated by a person or company approved to run such aircraft carriers is covered.
                            </p>
                            <h2 style="color: #1F497D; font-size: 7.2pt; margin-bottom: 10pt;">6.3 Total And Permanent Disability</h2>
                            <p style="font-size: 6pt; letter-spacing: 0.1pt; line-height: 12px; margin-bottom: 10pt;">
                                Total and Permanent Disablement shall be deemed to have arisen, if the Life Assured:
                            </p>
                            <ul style="list-style: none; padding-left: 15pt;">
                                <li style=" margin-bottom: 10pt; font-size: 6pt; letter-spacing: 0.1pt; line-height: 12px;">
                                    a) shall suffer the loss by physical severance of two limbs OR the sight of both eyes OR the loss by physical severance of one limb and the sight of one eye. (Limb shall mean leg, arm, entire hand or entire foot);
                                </li>
                                <li style=" margin-bottom: 10pt; font-size: 6pt; letter-spacing: 0.1pt; line-height: 12px;">
                                    b) has been absent through accident or disease from his/her employment for six consecutive months, and it is proved to the satisfaction of the Insurer that he/she has become so permanently incapacitated as to render it impossible for him/her ever to resume his/her employment or follow any other trade, profession or occupation.
                                </li>
                            </ul>
                            <p style="font-size: 6pt; letter-spacing: 0.1pt; line-height: 12px; margin-bottom: 10pt;">
                                The Insurer will pay the disability benefits covered as a lump sum and the liability of the Insurer under this policy shall be fully discharged without further action.
                            </p>
                            <p style="font-size: 6pt; letter-spacing: 0.1pt; line-height: 12px; margin-bottom: 10pt;">
                                The disability benefits as provided above, shall only apply to this policy while it is continued in force in its original form and if the policy is altered in any way, these disability benefits shall be automatically cancelled, but may be reinstated in the same or another form according to the terms of the policy as altered.
                            </p>
                            <p style="font-size: 6pt; letter-spacing: 0.1pt; line-height: 12px; margin-bottom: 10pt;">
                                The disability benefits, shall likewise not apply in the event of the disability being, directly or indirectly caused by or traceable to:-
                            </p>
                            <ul style="list-style: none; padding-left: 15pt;">
                                <li style=" margin-bottom: 5pt; font-size: 6pt; letter-spacing: 0.1pt; line-height: 12px;">
                                    a) Self-Inflicted Injury;
                                </li>
                                <li style=" margin-bottom: 5pt; font-size: 6pt; letter-spacing: 0.1pt; line-height: 12px;">
                                    b) Indulgence in alcohol;
                                </li>
                                <li style=" margin-bottom: 5pt; font-size: 6pt; letter-spacing: 0.1pt; line-height: 12px;">
                                    c) The use of drugs (other than as prescribed by a medical practitioner);
                                </li>
                                <li style=" margin-bottom: 5pt; font-size: 6pt; letter-spacing: 0.1pt; line-height: 12px;">
                                    d) Failure to follow medical advice
                                </li>
                                <li style=" margin-bottom: 5pt; font-size: 6pt; letter-spacing: 0.1pt; line-height: 12px;">
                                    e) Aerial sports and hazardous Pursuits
                                </li>
                                <li style=" margin-bottom: 5pt; font-size: 6pt; letter-spacing: 0.1pt; line-height: 12px;">
                                    f) Aviation Except as a Fare Paying Passenger on a Recognised Air Route
                                </li>
                                <li style=" margin-bottom: 5pt; font-size: 6pt; letter-spacing: 0.1pt; line-height: 12px;">
                                    g) Participation in Criminal Acts
                                </li>
                            </ul>
